cs.LG, cs.SY, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, cs.AI

The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms for optimal control of gene regulatory networks, which falls under the intersection of computer science and systems biology. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on adapting a reinforcement learning algorithm for this specific application. The second most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with the control of complex biological systems. The paper also mentions the use of computer simulations, which suggests a possible fit with q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) and q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs). Finally, the use of artificial intelligence techniques for control suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
